Note:
HTML Round-Trip Translation Test Suite

Tests bidirectional translation: HTML → HIR → HTML

Total Tests: 12
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/html/html_to_hir.runa" as ToHIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/html/hir_to_html.runa" as ToHTML
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/html/html_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/io/display.runa" as Display

@Reasoning:
Counter triple shared by the HTML round-trip driver. Identical layout
to peer translation test suites so a unified runner can swap test
binaries with no struct conversion.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
total at offset 0, passed at 8, failed at 16; mutated via raw
Layout.memory_set_int64 because results is shared by handle.
@End Implementation

Type called "TestResults":
    total as Integer
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Drives 12 HTML -> HIR -> HTML round-trip checks covering element
varieties (div, p, h1), attributes, self-closing tags, void elements
(img, br), nested DOMs, lists, comments, class attributes, input
elements, and DOCTYPE. Any emitter rule that loses information surfaces
as a re-parse failure on the second leg.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Initialize TestResults, print banner, then call test_round_trip with
each inline HTML snippet. Print summary and return 1 on any failure.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- "<div></div>" -> parse->HIR->emit->parse->HIR all succeed
- "<a href=\"#\">Link</a>" -> href attribute survives
- "<br />" -> self-closing form preserved
- "<!-- Comment -->" -> comment survives emit
- "<!DOCTYPE html>" -> DOCTYPE survives both legs
- Any malformed snippet -> "Initial parse failed", exit 1
@End TestCases

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type TestResults with total as 0, passed as 0, failed as 0

    proc print_header

    proc test_round_trip with "<div></div>", "Simple div", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<p>Hello</p>", "Paragraph with text", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<h1>Title</h1>", "Heading", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<a href=\"#\">Link</a>", "Link with attribute", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<br />", "Self-closing tag", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<img src=\"x.jpg\" />", "Image", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<div><p>Nested</p></div>", "Nested elements", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<ul><li>Item</li></ul>", "List", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<!-- Comment -->", "Comment", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<div class=\"x\"></div>", "Class attribute", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<input type=\"text\" />", "Input element", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<!DOCTYPE html>", "DOCTYPE", results

    proc print_results with results

    If results.failed is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Performs parse -> HIR -> emit -> re-parse -> HIR for one HTML fragment.
Both legs must reach HIR for the test to pass, proving the emitter
produced syntactically valid HTML that round-trips through the parser.
translate_html_to_hir accepts a 0 options argument and uses its own
scratch allocator internally, matching the CSS suite's approach.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. Increment results.total.
2. parse_html(source) -> ast1; null -> "Initial parse failed".
3. translate_html_to_hir(source, 0) -> hir1; null -> "Translation to HIR failed".
4. generate_html(hir1) -> generated; null -> "Generation from HIR failed".
5. parse_html(generated) -> ast2; null -> free generated, "Re-parse failed".
6. translate_html_to_hir(generated, 0) -> hir2; null -> free generated,
   "Re-translation to HIR failed".
7. Success: free generated, increment results.passed.
Note: each failure path tracks the exact buffers allocated up to that
point so deallocation is balanced. The inline HTML sources are static
string literals and are never freed.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- "<p>Hello</p>" -> all six stages succeed
- ")(not html" -> ast1 == 0 -> "Initial parse failed"
- Emitter drops the closing tag -> ast2 == 0 -> "Re-parse failed"
- Translator returns 0 on the second pass -> hir2 == 0 ->
  "Re-translation to HIR failed"
@End TestCases

Process called "test_round_trip" takes source as Integer, test_name as Integer, results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let ast1 be proc parse_html from Parser with source

    If ast1 is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Initial parse failed"
        Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hir1 be proc translate_html_to_hir from ToHIR with source, 0

    If hir1 is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Translation to HIR failed"
        Let _rfal2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal2 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let generated be proc generate_html from ToHTML with hir1

    If generated is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Generation from HIR failed"
        Let _rfal3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal3 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ast2 be proc parse_html from Parser with generated

    If ast2 is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Re-parse failed"
        proc deallocate from Layout with generated
        Let _rfal4 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal4 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hir2 be proc translate_html_to_hir from ToHIR with generated, 0

    If hir2 is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Re-translation to HIR failed"
        proc deallocate from Layout with generated
        Let _rfal5 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal5 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with generated

    proc print_test_success with test_name
    Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Banner emitted once at startup. Separator width (40 "=") matches the
title length so the heading lines up cleanly in CI logs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emit the title and the "=" rule via display_string (each on its own
line).
@End Implementation

Process called "print_header" returns Integer:
    proc display_string with "HTML Round-Trip Translation Test Suite"
    proc display_string with "========================================"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[PASS] <name>" line. Identical to peer HTML suites so unified greps
work across the language family.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emit "[PASS] " prefix with display_string_continuing (no newline), then
the caller-owned test_name with display_string (terminates the line).
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_success" takes test_name as Integer returns Integer:
    proc display_string_continuing with "[PASS] "
    proc display_string with test_name

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[FAIL] <name>: <reason>" line. reason identifies the exact round-trip
stage that broke (initial parse, translate, emit, re-parse, re-translate)
so failure logs pinpoint the responsible component.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emit "[FAIL] " prefix, test_name, ": " each with display_string_continuing
(no newline), then reason with display_string (terminates the line).
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_failure" takes test_name as Integer, reason as Integer returns Integer:
    proc display_string_continuing with "[FAIL] "
    proc display_string_continuing with test_name
    proc display_string_continuing with ": "
    proc display_string with reason

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Final summary block matching peer HTML suites. Reads counters through
type-checked struct field access (results.total etc.) at the report
site, complementing the raw memory_get_int64 path used in test_round_trip.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Print "=" separator, "Test Results:" heading, then Total/Passed/Failed
lines via display_string_continuing for labels and display_integer for
the counter values.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_results" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    proc display_string with "========================================"
    proc display_string with "Test Results:"

    proc display_string_continuing with "Total: "
    proc display_integer with results.total

    proc display_string_continuing with "Passed: "
    proc display_integer with results.passed

    proc display_string_continuing with "Failed: "
    proc display_integer with results.failed

    Return 1
End Process

Note: End of HTML Round-Trip Translation Test Suite
